article.headline: Miami (Ohio) 62, Valparaiso 50
article.story: OXFORD, Ohio -- Michael Bramos scored 28 points, going 6-of-9 from behind the 3-point arc, to lead Miami of Ohio to a 62-50 victory over Valparaiso on Saturday. Eric Pollitz added 11 for the RedHawks (6-3). Michael Rogers and Jake Diebler had 10 apiece for Valparaiso (3-6). Miami took the lead for good at 6-4 after less than 2 minutes, but led only 29-26 at the half. Valparaiso cut that to 1 twice early in the second half, both times on a layup by Rogers. But a jumper by Tyler Dierkers started a 10-3 run that included a pair of 3-pointers and a jumper by Bramos as Miami pulled away. A 3-pointer by Bramos gave Miami its biggest lead at 60-47 with 2:23 to play.
